<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">492. Hedgecoe, John. The Photographer's Handbook. New York: Alfred A. Knopf, 1977. 352 pp. Index, glossary, B/W illus., color illus. ISBN 0-394-40754-7. </p><p class="annot">This comprehensive reference manual of photographic techniques, procedures, equipment,and style is abundantly illustrated with black-and- white or color illustrations or photographs. Twenty pages are devoted to color photography, processing, and printing. The section on additive color and color usage includes a hue circle and information on complementary color, “discordant” color, saturation, dominant color, pasttern, and harmony. This book could be a useful starting point for beginning color photographers because of its wide variety of topics. </p></div>
